thread.title: Lackluster Hong Kong Debut May Bode Ill for Coming Tech IPOs

author: Joanne Chiu
title: Lackluster Hong Kong Debut May Bode Ill for Coming Tech IPOs
text: The lukewarm Hong Kong trading debut for Ping An Healthcare & Technology Co., the worst-performing major tech initial public offering globally in 2 ½ years, might point to investors’ cooling appetite for the sector as the U.S. and China fight over trade.
